Bosch Radionics D2112 Program

Programmable by Downloading, 5200 Programmer or by Keypad (2112 only)
Enter Program 1. Clip Standby switch on main board
2. Press 1, keypad should beep
3. Enter Installer Code (Default=654321, if Protect America use 1010)
(If Customer uses a 4-digit Code then Installer Code is only 4-digits)
4. Press 8 to enter program mode
Program Steps 1. Move to Program Group (1 to 13) by pressing Right Panic key
2. Use Number keys to select Location in Group (1 to 8), Zone light shows location
3. To view a Location press Middle Panic key, number lights will flash Value
4. Press Left Panic key to modify Location, Zone light will flash, enter data
5. Press Left Panic key again to save Location, Zone light will stop flashing
6. Use Number keys to select next Location or Right Panic for next Group
Delete Location Press CLEAR while in a Location
Answer
Download 		2 + Passcode
Hex Program While modifying a Location C+2=A, C+3=B, C+4=C, C+5=D, C+6=E, C+7=F
Exit Program Press CLEAR key, all Zone lights except 4 will turn ON, unclip Standby Switch
(System will now send a Reboot (R14) signal)
4/2 Signals CLICK HERE FOR LIST OF WHAT BELOW PROGRAMMING WILL REPORT
1. Account Group Default
1   Account Number (4-digits)
2 Phone 1 (up to 19 digits)
3 Phone 2 (up to 19 digits) Leave Blank
4 Download Phone (up to 19 Digits) Leave Blank
5 Download Passcode (999999)
6 Installer Code (654321)
7 Account Group Lock (0 = No, 1 = Yes) Locks out Keypad programming
8 Return to Default (0 = No, 1 = Yes)   Defaults all programming
2. Phone Group Default
1 DTMF Dialing (0 = No, 1 = Yes)
2 Answer w/Armed 5 Rings 5 times if Armed
3 Answer w/Disarmed 15 Rings 15 times if Disarmed
4 Answer Machine (0 = No, 1 = Yes) Enables Ring Hang, Ring Hang, Ring
5 Program Lock (0 = No, 1 = Yes) Locks Panel from Future programming
3. Receiver Format Group Default
1 Receiver Format 0 (0 or 1) 1 = Modem II, 0 = Pulse 4/2 format
2 Fire Group 1 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Fire Points 1 to 8 and Fire Panics
3 Non-Fire Group 3 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Non-Fire Points, and Non-Fire Panics
4 Point Trouble Group 6 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Trble/Bypass/Swinger on Points 1 to 8
5 Restoral Group 0 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Restoral on Fire/Non Fire Points 1 to 8
6 Closing Group 0 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Closing for Users 1 to 8, if needed use 4
7 Opening Group 0 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Opening for Users 1 to 8, if needed use 5
8 Cancel Group 0 (0 to 9, B to F) 1st digit of Cancel Report for Users 1 to 8
4 . Report Group for Pulse Default Point
1 Sys Trbl Group

You program 1st digit
Panel sends + what
is listed to the right

7 1 = Unsuccessful Download Attempt
2 = Automatic Test Timer Report
3 = Automatic Reset
4 = Short on Terminal 9, Aux Power, Fuse Open
5 = Short on Terminal 6, Alarm Output, Fuse Open
6 = Report Battery Missing
7 = Report Low Battery
8 = No AC Power
2 Sys Restore Group

You program 1st digit
Panel sends + what
is listed to the right

8 1 = Successful Download Attempt
2 = Successful Communication after Com Failure
3 = Panel Reset with Stand-By Switch
4 = Short Removed from Terminal 9, Aux Power Rest
5 = Short Removed from Terminal 6, Alarm Output
6 = Not Used
7 = Report Missing or Low Battery Restoral
8 = AC Power Restoral
3 Duress Rep Code 9 1 to 3 Not Used
4 = Report after 6 invalid Passcoda attempts
5 = Duress Code 8 entered at Keypad
7 to 8 Not Used
5. Reports Group Use
1 Delay Alarm Reports 0 0 to 255 Seconds
2 Cancel Report 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes
3 Restoral Reports 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes
4 Delay Rest Reports 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes
5 AC Fail Buzz/Reports 0 0 = No Buzzer or Report on AC Fai)
1 = Buzzer no Report
2 = Buzzer and Report
3 = Buzzer, Tag-Along Rep (sends with next Alarm/Trouble)
6. System Options Group Use
1 Disable System 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes (Allows re-enable by 5200 only, DO NOT USE)
2 Excursion 3 0 = Disabled (“Step Outside” Feature)
1 = All Inst
2 = Part Inst
3 = All & Part
3 Keyswitch 0 0 = Momentary
1 = Easikey, Momentary
7. Open Close Group Use
1 Entry Delay Time 30 0 to 255 seconds
2 Exit Delay Time 60 0 to 255 seconds
3 Exit Tone ? 0 = No, 1 = Yes
4 Op/CL Rep ALL On 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes (Open/Close Report if ALL (9) armed)
5 Op/Cl Rep PARTOn 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes (Open/Close Report if PART (0) armed)
6 Restricted Op/Close 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes (Opening Report if disarmed after alarm)
7 Bell Test 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes (Sounds Bell/Siren 2 seconds if ALL ON Armed)
8. A B C Keys Group Default
1 A Key Report (Police) 91 0 to 9 (These keys can be whatever you want)
2 B Key Report (Medical) 92 0 to 9 (Usually A = Police, B = Medical, C = Fire)
3 C Key Report (Fire) 93 0 to 9
4 A (Police) Panic Output 1 0 = No Output
1 = Steady Output
2 = Pulsed Output
5 B (Medical) Panic Output 0 0 = No Output
1 = Steady Output
2 = Pulsed Output
6 C (Fire) Panic Output 2 0 = No Output
1 = Steady Output
2 = Pulsed Output
9. Bell & Test Timer Group Default
1 Bell Output Time 6 0 to 255 Minutes
2 Single Ring 1 0 = Outputs Every Alarm
1 = 1 Output per Alarm Period
3 Alarm on 2 Fail Attempts 0 0 = No
1 = Alarm on 2 Failed Attempts at Comm
4 Test Interval 0 0 = No
1 = 1 Day
2 = 7 Days
3 = 28 Days
5 Hours to Next Test Rpt 0 0 to 23 Hours
6 Min to Next Test Rpt 0 0 to 59 Minutes
7 Defer Test Report 0 0 = No, 1 = Yes
10. Point Codes Default
1 Point 1 260 Most Common are
2 Point 2 882 Delay Door = 880
3 Point 3 882 Instant Door = 980
4 Point 4 982 Motion Zone = 780
5 Point 5 782 Fire (Verified) Zone = 260
6 Point 6 782 Audible Panic Zone = 420
7 Point 7 (D2112E only) 781 Silent Panic Zone = 520
8 Point 8 (D2112E only) 781
1st Digit = Zone Type
1 = Fire Zone 6 = Delay Zone
2 = Fire Zone w/Verification 7 = Interior Follower/Motion Zone
3 = Buzzer on Fault 8 = Delay Zone
4 = 24 Hr Audible 9 = Instant Zone
5 = 24 Hr Silent A = Keyswitch
2nd Digit = Alarm Response
0 = No Response
1 = Report Enabled
2 = Report Enabled/Alarm Report Delay
3 = Report Enable/Alarm Rep Dellay/Swinger Shutdown
4 = Report Enabled/Swinger Shutdown
5 = Alarm Output
6 = Report Enabled/Alarm Output
7 = Report Enabled/Alarm Report Delay/Alarm Output
8 = Report Enabled/Alarm Report Delay/Swinger Shutdown/Alarm Output
9 = Report Enabled/Swinger Shutdown/Alarm Output
3rd Digit = Special Point (Zone) Options
0 = Disabled
1 = Trouble on Open
2 = Trouble on Short
3 = Trouble on Open or Short
4 = Double Knock (2 Violations before Alarm)
5 = Trouble on Open/Double Knock
6 = Trouble on Short/Double Knock
7 = Trouble on Open or Short/Double Knock

11. Relays Default
1 Relay 1 Func 1 0 0 = No Relay Output
1 = Alarm
2 = Alarm Memory
3 = Point Trouble
4 = Follow Point
5 = Watch Tone
6 = A, B, C Keys Steady Relay Output
7 = A, B, C Keys Momentary Relay Output
8 = A, B, C Keys Momentary Relay Output
9 = Off with Passcode
10 = Follow Alarm Output
11 = Pulses during E/E delay if ALL ON Armed, on until Disarmed
12 = Pulses during E/E delay if PART ON Armed, on until Disarmed
13 = Activate for 4 seconds if User Resets system
2 Relay 1 Func 2 0
3 Relay 2 Func 1 0
4 Relay 2 Func 2 0
12. Relay Parameter Group Default
1 Relay 1, Function 1 0 Requires D133 Module
2 Relay 1, Function 2 0
3 Relay 2, Function 1 0
4 Relay 2, Function 2 0
13. User Config Group Default
1 User Test/Bell? 1 (0=No, 1=Yes) Allows User to do Siren Test
2 User Test/Battery? 1 (0=No, 1=Yes) Allows User to do Battery Test
3 User Test/Comm? 1 (0=No, 1=Yes) Allows User to do Communication Test
4 Passcode Length 4 (3=3-Digit User Codes, 4=4-Digit, 5=5-Digit, 6=6 Digit
5 User Code 8 is Duress 1 (0=No, 1=Yes)
6 Passcode Required ? (0=No Code Req to Arm, 1=Code Required)
7 Change Passcode 1 (0=No Code changes, 1=Owner changes, 2=Owner/User changes)
14. Passcodes Group (Only available with 5200 Program or by Downloading!)
1 = User # Type Disabled/Owner/User/One-Time
2 = User # Passcode
